Title: 'Drug kingpins' to be extradited to Australia, court in Dubai orders
Summary: The court has approved the extradition to Australia of two Sydney men over their role in an alleged major drug importation ring.

Title: Former CSIRO worker avoids jail for using supercomputers to mine cryptocurrency
Summary: The man's activities diverted computing power from important scientific projects and netted him $9400 worth of cryptocurrency.

Title: Two men charged after meth packages intercepted in Brisbane, Perth
Summary: It is alleged a large amount of the total 12 kilograms of methamphetamine seized was concealed within furniture parts.

Title: 'Not all Australians are the good guys': Citizens in cyber spy agency's sights
Summary: The head of Australia's cyber spy agency will declare it has been collecting intelligence on Australians for at least 20 years.

Title: Racing officials probe horse racing outfit over cryptocurrency scam
Summary: Phoenix Thoroughbreds, which co-owns Australian Group 1 winner Farnan who is trained by Gai Waterhouse, was banned from racing in France earlier this month after a prosecution witness alleged in a New York court that its Dubai-based owner Amer Abdulaziz Salman had stolen $161 million in the OneCoin cryptocurrency scheme.

Title: Police probe possible organised crime consortium behind alleged cocaine haul
Summary: After Border Force noticed a suspicious-looking boat route, police raided a fishing vessel to allegedly find 1.8 tonnes of cocaine on board - and three men not previously known to police

Title: Police find tonne of suspected cocaine after tracing boat on suspicious route
Summary: When investigators boarded the Coralynne, they found a fire in the engine room and what they allege was more than a tonne of drugs in the boat, unconcealed.

Title: Porter defends Keelty's appointment to anti-corruption position
Summary: Attorney-General Christian Porter has defended former AFP boss Mick Keelty's role as an anti-corruption adviser, even though his conduct was subject to a corruption investigation at the time.

Title: Compromised war crimes investigation is a stain on Australia's honour
Summary: Mick Keelty's sharing of confidential information about an investigation into war crimes in Afghanistan to former SAS veteran Ben Roberts-Smith must be investigated properly.

Title: Covert war crimes inquiry compromised by former AFP chief Mick Keelty
Summary: A corruption investigation was launched after confidential police information was leaked to war crimes suspect Ben Roberts-Smith at a covert stage of the inquiry.
